The Twilight

The twilight falls in colors deep,  
   Hues of violet and gold;  
As the world begins to slumber  
   New stories shall unfold.

Let me wander in your wonder,  
   Until the stars awake;  
In this peaceful, quiet moment,  
   My heart shall gently break.

- Bliss Carman
